McKie Leaves Merrill as Head Emissions Trader, Sparkspread Says

-- B y   M a t h e w   C a r r
-- 
2011-03-09T16:54:53Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-09/mckie-leaves-merrill-as-head-emissions-trader-sparkspread-says.html
Iain McKie, head of European
emissions trading at  Bank of America Corp. (BAC) ’s Merrill Lynch, has
left as part of a reorganization of the bank’s carbon desk,
according to the news service Sparkspread.  Merrill Lynch hired McKie last year to trade greenhouse-
gas contracts,  according to the report . He was previously a
trader at Balyasny Asset Management LP and RNK Capital LLC, both
hedge fund managers, it said.    Andrew Todd , a London-based spokesman at Merrill Lynch,
declined to comment when contacted by Bloomberg News.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Mathew Carr in Copenhagen via 
